The OnDemand unified interface (with all of the application icons for each of the suites on one page) is not available to users who download and install all of the application as standalone instances.

To make it easier for new team members to get up to speed with the Atlassian suite of products as well as make it easier to switch between applications in an integrated Atlassian setup, as a user I would like to have the ability to setup an integrated, standalone Atlassian application suite to look like the OnDemand interface.

When performing a simple search in the issue navigator, under section "Dates & Times" we have the option to filter an issue using _Created After_ and _Created Before_ parameters. The expected behavior is to filter the issues created *after* the date informed in the _Created After_ parameter and created *before* the date informed in the _Created Before_ parameter.

However, after performing this search on the simple searching mode we click under *Switch to advanced searching*, the search parameters are changed to

{code:sql}
project = TST AND created >= 2012-02-12 AND created <= 2012-02-14
{code}

Under Advanced searching mode it is including the 2012-02-12 and 2012-02-14 as date range, using the "=", when it shouldn't, and in the since in Simple searching mode makes you think it is not, since it uses _Created After_ and _Created Before_.

